 the teachings are always pointing out to us to remember. So we're not too caught up in

00:01:18.380 --> 00:01:29.020
 the gross kind of rough illusion. It's to remember the wisdom of the Buddhist teachings

00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:40.020
 and the big, big, beautiful, true view that we all have Buddha nature, that our innate

00:01:40.020 --> 00:01:51.960
 nature is limitless wisdom, intelligence, inseparable from loving kindness and the capacity to imme

00:01:51.960 --> 00:01:52.420
asurably

00:01:52.420 --> 00:02:00.000
 benefit every living being who doesn't recognize their true nature and help mature them, bring

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:08.640
 them to that realization. We all have beautiful nature. Again, it's just the degree to which

00:02:08.640 --> 00:02:16.900
 we recognize it or not is the only difference. So, like it says in one of the tantras of

00:02:16.900 --> 00:02:27.160
 the Buddha, the Heavantra Tantra, all beings are Buddhas by nature, but it's temporarily

00:02:27.160 --> 00:02:37.860
 concealed by advantageous stains of perception. So, I mean, that's just such a critically

00:02:37.860 --> 00:02:43.260
 important thing to recognize as we take refuge in the three jewels and the three roots and

00:02:43.260 --> 00:02:51.320
 in our practice, is having some degree of more confidence and trust in the truth of

00:02:51.320 --> 00:02:57.660
 the Buddha's realization. But at the heart of that is our own potential and our own just

00:02:57.660 --> 00:03:06.900
 natural goodness is there at the heart of everything, whether we recognize it or not.

00:03:06.900 --> 00:03:15.580
 And so, really, it's said in the teachings that the path of awakening to our bodhicitta,

00:03:15.580 --> 00:03:24.900
 to our absolute bodhicitta, to our true Buddhahood, to realizing the great perfection, that path

00:03:24.900 --> 00:03:35.300
 is really removing our obscurations. As we remove our obscurations in the teachings,

00:03:35.300 --> 00:03:46.300
 our innate Buddha nature, innate wisdom and our natural compassion, all of those qualities

00:03:46.300 --> 00:03:55.700
 we all have are more fully developed and shining, the more our obscurations are revealed. Our

00:03:55.700 --> 00:04:04.620
 obscurations are revealed to us and then we remove them. So, that's really that point.

00:04:04.620 --> 00:04:11.200
 If we didn't have Buddha nature, there'd be no reason to practice. Our Buddha nature

00:04:11.200 --> 00:04:22.080
 is the cause of our enlightenment. So, that's just like the example when we have dirty hands,

00:04:22.080 --> 00:04:30.220
 it's not that our hands are dirty, it's that we have dirt on our hands as a rough metaphor.

00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:36.060
 When a window is really dirty and hard to see through, it's not that the window itself

00:04:36.060 --> 00:04:43.100
 is dirty, it's that there's dirt on the window and we wash it. And if we put all those ingredients

00:04:43.100 --> 00:04:53.940
 together, the soap, the water, the friction, the rinse, then the result is there. We see

00:04:53.940 --> 00:04:59.980
 what was there to begin with. And so, that's, I think, really important to remember as we're

00:04:59.980 --> 00:05:20.540
 practicing. Our obscurations are what obscures us from recognizing our Buddha nature. So,

00:05:20.540 --> 00:05:25.860
 the Buddha initially gave, the very first teaching the Buddha gave in this human world,

00:05:25.860 --> 00:05:36.820
 the Four Noble Truths, the truth of suffering, the truth that there's not just suffering

00:05:36.820 --> 00:05:48.600
 and challenges, but there's causes for suffering and challenges. Those causes are our

00:05:48.600 --> 00:05:50.980
 misunderstanding

00:05:50.980 --> 00:06:00.860
 of things as they are, our ego clinging, our negative emotions and grasping are what perpetuate

00:06:00.860 --> 00:06:11.640
 our suffering, which perpetuate our samsara. So, samsara and suffering and obscurations,

00:06:11.640 --> 00:06:18.340
 they're all one and the same. Then, of course, the Buddha didn't just teach their suffering

00:06:18.340 --> 00:06:25.020
 and causes for suffering. He's pointing out from the most basic Buddhism and then just

00:06:25.020 --> 00:06:30.760
 becomes more and more direct what the Buddha is pointing out and directing, ushering our

00:06:30.760 --> 00:06:39.100
 minds towards realizing is that there's freedom from suffering. There's cessation of suffering,

00:06:39.100 --> 00:06:48.380
 the truth of cessation of suffering. And then there's causes for that. There's ways and

00:06:48.380 --> 00:06:57.540
 methods to remove the causes of our suffering and bring out our innate nature. And so that's

00:06:57.540 --> 00:07:06.380
 what the path we have, these are the teachings we have to explore and to try out and apply

00:07:06.380 --> 00:07:20.340
 to our lives. How beautiful. And so again, just kind of returning to that point, its

00:07:20.340 --> 00:07:33.390
 obscurations are samsara, who samsara are samsara. Everything comes down to our own mind and

00:07:33.390 --> 00:07:34.260
 recognizing

00:07:34.260 --> 00:07:42.980
 its qualities and removing our obscurations. And so all of our nundro practice is doing

00:07:42.980 --> 00:07:48.720
 that. And then with the Vajrasattva section in particular, we're kind of really focusing

00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:55.060
 on that. But again, as we'll talk as we go, none of the nundro is kind of really completely

00:07:55.060 --> 00:08:09.740
 separate from another. It's all bringing out beautiful aspects of that one whole practice.

00:08:09.740 --> 00:08:23.960
 So again, I took a few little notes so I didn't get too lost in space here. So as far as obsc

00:08:23.960 --> 00:08:24.380
urations

