 again, what makes all the difference is how much each one of us, myself included, really

00:09:12.380 --> 00:09:21.060
 contemplates this and really brings it to heart. So what are the two obscurations? They're

00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:34.620
 called emotional obscurations and conceptual obscurations or knowledge obscurations. Emotional

00:09:34.620 --> 00:09:43.380
 and conceptual. Emotional obscurations are much more rough, much more kind of our outer

00:09:43.380 --> 00:09:50.820
 samsara experience, the real rough stuff we notice first and engage with most often. But

00:09:50.820 --> 00:09:58.860
 of course it's all based on our knowledge obscurations, our very, very, very subtle

00:09:58.860 --> 00:10:06.260
 obscurations that are, you know, come right down to our basic not knowing. But now these

00:10:06.260 --> 00:10:14.500
 two obscurations are sometimes broken down into four obscurations where emotional obscurations

00:10:14.500 --> 00:10:23.780
 can be looked at two ways and conceptual obscurations looked at two ways. And so that's known as

00:10:23.780 --> 00:10:29.180
 karmic obscurations as far as the emotional obscurations can be broken down, kind of to

00:10:29.180 --> 00:10:33.420
 look at a little bit more, parse them out a little bit more, look at them a little more

00:10:33.420 --> 00:10:44.980
 clearly. Karmic obscurations and then our negative emotions, the obscurations of our

00:10:44.980 --> 00:10:52.420
 negative emotions. So our karmic obscurations are, again, the word karmic is there because

00:10:52.420 --> 00:11:04.740
 they're involved with our actions, our actions of body, speech, mind. And right, so those

00:11:04.740 --> 00:11:14.140
 are all caused by how we see things, our emotions, how much ignorance we have, how much hope

00:11:14.140 --> 00:11:24.560
 and fear we have, how many actions of our bodies and speech and habitual mind we have.

00:11:24.560 --> 00:11:32.180
 And so one way of understanding that is kind of from the ordinary level for every being

00:11:32.180 --> 00:11:38.300
 whatsoever there's two kinds of karmic obscurations or two kinds of ways in which we act that

00:11:38.300 --> 00:11:44.580
 cause more trouble for ourselves and others directly and indirectly. And those are sometimes

00:11:44.580 --> 00:11:56.900
 called natural, kind of natural karmic activities and kind of fabricated. So what does that

00:11:56.900 --> 00:12:08.780
 mean? So natural karmic activities are things like killing, stealing, abusive behavior,

00:12:08.780 --> 00:12:17.180
 hatred, you know, hatred, thoughts and actions, for example. That's all no matter what everybody's

00:12:17.180 --> 00:12:26.220
 harmed, we're harmed, others are harmed, doesn't matter. And then what's called more fabricated

00:12:26.220 --> 00:12:32.940
 karma is then more involved with our mind and as dharma practitioners. On the basic

00:12:32.940 --> 00:12:43.240
 level that means when we make a promise and go against it. And so then on levels of taking

00:12:43.240 --> 00:12:48.340
 the Buddhist teachings that would mean, you know, so in other words also that could be

00:12:48.340 --> 00:12:55.580
 all the kind of customs and laws and regulations just in the ordinary world and wherever we

00:12:55.580 --> 00:13:02.180
 are, those are kind of acting against those can cause us trouble on some degree, right.

00:13:02.180 --> 00:13:08.900
 And then on the spiritual level, when we begin to take like vows of the pratimoksha, whether

00:13:08.900 --> 00:13:18.020
 we're lay or non or monk, the vows we take there as the path of individual liberation,

00:13:18.020 --> 00:13:29.460
 not to kill, not to steal, not avoid sexual misconduct, you know, etc, etc. And then the

00:13:29.460 --> 00:13:40.420
 vows we can take as bodhisattva, seeing every single being as our mother, really engaging

00:13:40.420 --> 00:13:50.180
 with the bodhicitta, all the vows we take as bodhisattva, all our bodhisattva vows in conviction.

00:13:50.180 --> 00:14:00.500
 And then what we take on as Vajrayana practitioners of the purity. These are examples of fabricated

00:14:00.500 --> 00:14:00.500
.

00:14:00.500 --> 00:14:06.900
 But when it's so involved again, what makes all the difference with karma, the Buddha

00:14:06.900 --> 00:14:14.500
 taught is how we feel about our actions, how much we think about them when we think and

00:14:14.500 --> 00:14:21.940
 how we really feel about them, when we whether it's positive, negative, neutral. If we think

00:14:21.940 --> 00:14:28.300
 about doing something and we feel good about it, that's first really powerful ingredient

00:14:28.300 --> 00:14:35.220
 for powerful karma. When we think about something and feel good about it, and then we do it,

00:14:35.220 --> 00:14:40.780
 and we feel good about it as we're doing it, that makes it even more powerful. When we

00:14:40.780 --> 00:14:47.100
 continue that action and bring it to fulfillment and still feel good about it, that makes it

00:14:47.100 --> 00:14:53.980
 all the most powerful, it's going to have the most powerful effect for ourselves and

00:14:53.980 --> 00:15:12.740
 others and ultimately, you know, in our own experience. And so, that's just something

00:15:12.740 --> 00:15:22.140
 to keep in mind with looking at our karmic, karmic obscurations. And they do intersect,

00:15:22.140 --> 00:15:31.100
 for example, in the teachings, it's taught, for example, killing. Every people are harmed

00:15:31.100 --> 00:15:38.700
 when we kill, but if we haven't taken a vow not to kill out of great reverence for life,

00:15:38.700 --> 00:15:43.060
 then maybe killing doesn't have quite the same karmic effect as if someone who's really

00:15:43.060 --> 00:15:52.780
 vowed not to kill. And then again, just being sober and like really recognizing the magnitude

00:15:52.780 --> 00:16:00.060
 and the beautiful power of our practice when we have our bodhicitta intention and motivation

00:16:00.060 --> 00:16:06.300
 and conviction and a vow in front of all the Buddhas and bodhisattvas to actualize our

00:16:06.300 --> 00:16:14.940
 bodhicitta for the benefit of all living beings. If we kill, what is that doing? That's even

00:16:14.940 --> 00:16:21.620
 more powerfully going against kind of these vows. And then on the Vajrayana level, seeing

00:16:21.620 --> 00:16:28.740
 all the apparent existence, all phenomena as the pure mandala of all the Buddhas, three

00:16:28.740 --> 00:16:37.860
 Kaya mandala, then what are we doing when we kill? Again, we can get complicated, but the

00:16:37.860 --> 00:16:45.180
 point is all of the vows we take are to help usher us, to help protect us, to help keep

00:16:45.180 --> 00:16:52.300
 us on the path. But they're beautiful, powerful means, you know, skillful means for bringing

00:16:52.300 --> 00:17:01.380
 out our goodness qualities and cherishing our motivation and our intention is so important

00:17:01.380 --> 00:17:06.620
 and beautiful. That's what's going to always bring us back to the right path and make all

00:17:06.620 --> 00:17:12.860
 the difference for the future, no matter what mistakes we make. So anyway, I was talking

00:17:12.860 --> 00:17:19.620
 about habitual, no, about karmic obscurations. And then of course, emotional obscurations

00:17:19.620 --> 00:17:26.380
 are the other part of that, the breakdown. And what are our emotional obscurations? That's

00:17:26.380 --> 00:17:33.700
 essentially we could look at the 84,000 emotions, which can be summarized as the five poisons

00:17:33.700 --> 00:17:49.660
 or the five basic emotions, ignorance, attachment, arrogance, jealousy, anger, you know, and

00:17:49.660 --> 00:17:59.340
 that can be broken down into the three basic emotions of ignorance, aversion, attachment,

00:17:59.340 --> 00:18:06.860
 you know, that basic again, the basic not knowing of ignorance. And then keeping that

00:18:06.860 --> 00:18:14.060
 in all of our actions of hope and fear, it's those things that propel all of our karmic

00:18:14.060 --> 00:18:21.700
 obscurations. So the less ego clinging we have, the less grasping we have, the more

00:18:21.700 --> 00:18:28.420
 we contemplate the teachings and practice, the more we're, we're more likely to refrain

00:18:28.420 --> 00:18:36.780
 from harm, engage and benefit, take responsibility for our own mind and our own actions and our

00:18:36.780 --> 00:18:46.300
 own liberation, and with the motivation to benefit others. And then again, just to go

00:18:46.300 --> 00:18:52.940
 a little bit more quickly now, as far as looking at the two obscurations as for like we talked

00:18:52.940 --> 00:19:00.140
 about, emotional obscurations looked at as karmic and emotional. And now as far as our

00:19:00.140 --> 00:19:07.180
 conceptual obscurations, that's again, on a little more very subtle level, looking on

00:19:07.180 --> 00:19:17.740
 more subtle level of our samsara. That has to do with our basic ignorance and misperception

00:19:17.740 --> 00:19:24.420
 of how things are. So that can be broken down into what's called conceptual obscurations,

00:19:24.420 --> 00:19:31.020
 and then the habitual obscurations. Our conceptual obscurations, really the way that's summed

00:19:31.020 --> 00:19:40.780
 up in the teachings is, that's the habit we all have of subject, object, action. I am,

00:19:40.780 --> 00:19:48.180
 the world exists, and there's the interactions between that we substantially, that I exist,

00:19:48.180 --> 00:19:54.460
 the world substantially exists, and there's activity. On whatever level, that habitual

00:19:54.460 --> 00:20:02.380
 pattern is an obscuration, because the Buddha taught, that's actually not how things are

00:20:02.380 --> 00:20:12.340
 deep down. It's vast freedom, always shining, always moving. And then the fourth obscuration

00:20:12.340 --> 00:20:22.180
 is more the habitual, and that is very, very, very, very subtle conceptual obscurations,

00:20:22.180 --> 00:20:31.380
 kind of very subtle echoes of these conceptual obscurations that are purified. It's sometimes

00:20:31.380 --> 00:20:38.980
 said that that's like if you have a box that had perfume in it, or a bottle with perfume,

00:20:38.980 --> 00:20:45.680
 and there's no more perfume, but you still smell the fragrance. It's like that level.

00:20:45.680 --> 00:20:53.580
 So again, the point of this is too, all we've heard as our progress on the path from beginning

00:20:53.580 --> 00:21:00.340
 up through realizing the true nature to total Buddhahood, when we look at that from the

00:21:00.340 --> 00:21:08.820
 point of obscurations, that's like the Buddha pointed out, right? These kind of signposts

00:21:08.820 --> 00:21:14.380
 and indications of our progress on the path, and as far as how that relates to removing

00:21:14.380 --> 00:21:21.740
 our obscurations, if we start by cutting down our rough activity of listening to the teachings,

00:21:21.740 --> 00:21:28.140
 applying the teachings, gradually we take them on more and more, we're purifying, we're

00:21:28.140 --> 00:21:35.740
 refraining from harm, engaging in benefit, generating merit, generating our wisdom and

00:21:35.740 --> 00:21:42.440
 purifying by those means. And then there's what's called the five paths, or one way of

00:21:42.440 --> 00:21:51.820
 the Buddha showed us of progressing the kind of a basic map for signposts of our realization.

00:21:51.820 --> 00:21:59.480
 And when we first begin, those five paths are what, the path of accumulation, the path of

00:21:59.480 --> 00:22:12.420
 joining, the path of seeing, the path of meditation, the path of no more learning. So one way in

00:22:12.420 --> 00:22:17.100
 the teachings, again, this is kind of just as a way of connecting with seeing how removing

00:22:17.100 --> 00:22:23.620
 our obscurations and the causes of our obscurations, the causes of our suffering, the causes of

00:22:23.620 --> 00:22:39.460
 our challenges, the causes of our mess, that's the path. And so, for example, when we perfected

00:22:39.460 --> 00:22:46.780
 the path of accumulation, maybe that's when we've really cut, really truly, deeply cut

00:22:46.780 --> 00:22:59.300
 off our karmic obscurations. And then when we've really, really perfected the path of

00:22:59.300 --> 00:23:10.060
 joining an application, we've really perfected and cleaned away, totally abandoned our emotional

00:23:10.060 --> 00:23:17.980
 obscurations. And that means, right, then the next, the path of seeing, when we see the

00:23:17.980 --> 00:23:29.140
 great emptiness as it is, subject, object, action, beyond all, any way we could stand

00:23:29.140 --> 00:23:35.860
 it up or see it intellectually, see the true nature as it is, the great emptiness, so clear

00:23:35.860 --> 00:23:47.220
 and vibrant. That's when our conceptual habitual, our conceptual obscurations are purified. And

00:23:47.220 --> 00:23:52.060
 then again, in the path of meditation, moving up through all the bhoomis, that's when these

00:23:52.060 --> 00:23:58.900
 very, very subtle obscurations are purified. And when that happens, then it's the path

00:23:58.900 --> 00:24:04.460
 of no more learning, which is to say, there's no more to purify. All our naturally inherent

00:24:04.460 --> 00:24:12.060
 enlightened qualities are fully awakened, fully developed, completely purified. We're

00:24:12.060 --> 00:24:20.020
 Buddhists and we're object of refuge for all beings, just acting naturally for the benefit

00:24:20.020 --> 00:24:28.860
 of beings appearing to them as needed. And now, as ordinary sentient beings, we're in

00:24:28.860 --> 00:24:38.220
 the beautiful place of having a teacher, of having these perfect teacher who has so beautifully

00:24:38.220 --> 00:24:51.240
 maintained these beautiful, precious teachings that help us to awaken to that. And so, like

00:24:51.240 --> 00:25:01.240
 I'm getting at, obscurations are our samsara. Removing them, purifying our obscurations

00:25:01.240 --> 00:25:10.020
 is the path. Another word that Rinpoche uses often, you know, for obscurations and kind

00:25:10.020 --> 00:25:19.820
 of violations of our vows and Samayas and our promises is mistakes. So recognizing our

00:25:19.820 --> 00:25:32.260
 mistakes is the path, a big part of the path and how beautiful we shouldn't be afraid.

00:25:32.260 --> 00:25:39.860
 Because again, like the Buddha taught, there's more than suffering and its causes. Our fundamental

